<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="646" type="discussion">
<paragraph lastBlockId="27.[190,1397,2640,3463]" pageId="27" pageNumber="646">
This species was previously divided into three subspecies (
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1917" box="[1069,1168,2364,2397]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="646" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chapini">chapini</taxonomicName>
, shortridge, lancaster); indeed, race shortridge: has even been considered a separate species. However, pending further study, A. Monadjem and coauthors in 2010 and the African 
<taxonomicName authority="Report" authorityName="Report" box="[804,1069,2561,2594]" class="Chiroptera" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="27" pageNumber="646" phylum="Chordata" rank="class">Chiroptera Report</taxonomicName>
of 2017 are provisionally followed here in treating this complex as a single monotypic species; the £0is in need of revision. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
